property_description: Situated on a highly desirable street in Noe Valley, this new construction home has been thoughtfully built with an eye on high design and functionality. Spanning over 4 floors and with an elevator from the garage to the upper floor ensures that the home provides the flexibility needed for today's living. Upon entering it is immediately evident that the finishes are unique, timeless, and offer a sense of warmth and richness, not seen in many new homes. Warm wood panels, stylized staircase, solid stone and marble sinks, custom lighting features, large picture windows and doors are just some of the many design elements. A large living and dining area seamlessly integrate with a Chef's kitchen while offering outlooks to the landscaped yard with custom bench seating, thoughtful landscaping and a built-in BBQ. The entry foyer features two story ceilings with skylight, & opens directly into the main living space. The well-appointed kitchen includes modern appliances, honed counters, & a pantry. An inspired collaboration between owner & artist led to the design, & installation of a one-of-a-kind kitchen workspace & table. Adjacent to the kitchen, a wood counter island almost doubles the available work space in the kitchen. Below the counter is a second table, ingeniously designed w/ an iron wheel, fittings, & anchor point which pivots out to create an amazing dining table. The aesthetic of the design & materials marries perfectly with the character of the residence. The living room offers a vaulted & wood-paneled ceiling, new custom double-paned windows wrapped by a brick wall bring in wonderful natural light. One full, updated bath w/ shower over tub complete this level. The upper level includes a spacious, loft-style bedroom, generous closet space with washer / dryer, a modern & well-appointed full bath, & an additional storage room. Located on a tree lined street, this property is near many of the vibrant Inner Mission's offerings. Unit includes one car parking.

property_description: Just two blocks from 24th street's restaurants and shops, this rare 2-level condo is a quiet retreat from the bustle of Noe Valley. Occupying the entire front of the building, the condo has a unique position that shares nearly no interior walls with its surrounding neighbors, giving it a sense of privacy and the appeal of a single-family home. An ideal floor plan, all of the home's primary living spaces are on the main floor while the second floor becomes a sanctuary that includes 2 ensuite bedrooms and an office area. The generous chef's kitchen features quartz counters and a long breakfast bar, a SubZero fridge and SubZero 30-bottle wine fridge. A sunny balcony beckons off the dining room with floor-to-ceiling sliding doors, while the living room's fireplace and custom cabinetry create a cozy spot to lounge. A flexible use office or media room and updated powder room round out the floor. The primary bathroom features a steam shower, jetted soaking tub, and dual vanities for maximum relaxation. With a beautifully landscaped shared garden and firepit, storage, and 1 car parking this condo is both highly functional and extremely comfortable.

property_description: Just two blocks from 24th street's restaurants and shops, this rare 2-level condo is a quiet retreat from the bustle of Noe Valley. Occupying the entire front of the building, the condo has a unique position that shares nearly no interior walls with its surrounding neighbors, giving it a sense of privacy and the appeal of a single-family home. An ideal floor plan, all of the home's primary living spaces are on the main floor while the second floor becomes a sanctuary that includes 2 ensuite bedrooms and an office area. The generous chef's kitchen features quartz counters and a long breakfast bar, a SubZero fridge and SubZero 30-bottle wine fridge. A sunny balcony beckons off the dining room with floor-to-ceiling sliding doors, while the living room's fireplace and custom cabinetry create a cozy spot to lounge. A flexible use office or media room and updated powder room round out the floor. The primary bathroom features a steam shower, jetted soaking tub, and dual vanities for maximum relaxation. With a beautifully landscaped shared garden and firepit, storage, and 1 car parking this condo is both highly functional and extremely comfortable.

Carefully curated light fixtures including crystal chandeliers and sconces add to the special ambiance. The impeccably remodeled kitchen features Carrara marble counters, glass front cabinets, subway tile backsplash and stainless appliances, including a gas range. The dining nook has been transformed into a charming wine tasting room, with marble island, wine fridge and racks, and a beamed ceiling. Both the living room and the serene and spacious bedroom have triple paned windows that block City noise. A bonus office space and a vintage tile bath with marble vanity complete the well thought out floor plan that lives large. The Marina Chateau is known for its exquisite Spanish Mediterranean lobby and facade. The elevator building has a wind-protected common roof deck with stunning views of the Golden Gate Bridge. The ideal Cow Hollow location is near restaurants, shops, parks and transit making this the perfect San Francisco home!

Amenities include one-car parking, storage, Nest thermostat, tankless water heater and shared garden with its vibrant bougainvillea, star jasmine and lime tree. This is a fantastic neighborhood location that's also near transit and freeways.

property_description: Perched on the north side of one of the most sought-after and prestigious blocks in Pacific Heights, 2652 Broadway is set back from the tree-lined street behind its private gated driveway and entry. This exquisite residence offers expansive views and incredible natural light captured by its oversized windows, soaring ceilings, and grand scale. The main level presents a formal foyer, grand living room with southeast city views & a beautiful fireplace, a spacious dining room with bay views, a guest bedroom or office & bathroom, and a large eat-in kitchen with direct access to the charming rear garden. A grand staircase leads to the bedroom level with a primary suite that has southeast views, two ensuite bathrooms, and ample closet space. The second and third bedrooms, one with an ensuite bathroom and the other with built-in shelving, have serene northern views. The main staircase eventually leads to the unwarranted roof deck with panoramic views. The bottom level consists of a large 2-car garage and bonus room with ensuite bathroom and separate garden entrance. In close proximity to the city's premier dining, retail and parks, this home represents San Francisco living at its finest.

property_description: Live your best life mere steps from Dolores Park in this sprawling one bedroom condo with bonus space. This Edwardian style 4 unit building sits in the heart of the Mission Dolores neighborhood and boasts a coveted private garage. This unit also has more storage space than you will ever need. The main level consists of a large and sunny kitchen with wraparound countertops, ample cupboard space, dishwasher and adjacent dining area. Directly off of the kitchen is a classic living room with period built-in cabinetry, original molding and wood panels. Also on this level is a front facing bedroom with bay window bench. The recently remodeled bathroom has an all tile shower, new medicine cabinet and tile floor. This home does not stop on the first floor! Downstairs there is endless exclusive storage space and a massive bonus room. The seller has approved plans to add a finished room and bathroom downstairs, just waiting for the new owner to do the work. Along with the bonus room there are two other storage rooms, one of which includes private laundry. Also on this level is your own private one car garage. Steps from the incredible shops and restaurants of the Mission. Easy access to 101, 280 and 80 freeways. See why everyone loves Mission Dolores!

Featuring a stylish kitchen with recessed halogen lighting, stone countertops, custom wine storage and stainless steel appliances, there is a raised bedroom space with outfitted closet, as well as a full bath with attached in-unit laundry & outfitted storage closet. This condominium features may finishes that remind you of a NYC SoHo-style loft conversion. There is a shared roof-top terrace with lounge areas, dining table and grill. There is a high-tech video entry system, key-security elevator and this unit includes 1-car assigned parking. Located near tech offices, restaurants, night-life, it offers easy highway access. This is a unique, historic, beautiful place to make your nest. Property is open concept, tax records indicate no bedroom nor bathroom count. Commerial space condo houses Basil Canteen Restaurant on Street level.
Directions to Property: Property is located on the corner of Folsom and 11th St. The building address is 1489 Folsom St. but the entrance is on 11th St. (There is a video entry system).
Master Bathroom Features: Walk-In Closet, Tub w/Shower Over, Tile

property_description: Prepare to be impressed! Experience urban chic in this top-floor west-facing loft flooded w/ natural light & showcasing breathtaking views of Twin Peaks, Sutro Tower & rolling hills. Located in vibrant South Beach, this spacious 1-bed, 2-bath condo offers an unparalleled urban living experience. The main level features a formal entry w/ skylight, open living/dining/kitchen w/ soaring ceilings, gas fireplace, built-in shelving & outdoor balcony, a gourmet kitchen w/ sleek countertops, ample cabinetry, and s/s appliances, spacious dining area w/ b'fast bar, and a full bathroom with concrete flooring & shower over tub. The upper-level loft boasts a large mezzanine bedroom w/ generously sized walk-in closet, potential office area adjacent to bedroom, full bathroom w/ stall shower & granite vanity. Add'l features: refinished hardwood flooring, concrete flooring (kitchen, common bath), custom paint, modern window shades, recessed & contemporary lighting, laundry closet w/ stacked w/d, 1-car parking, and 2 expansive storages. The building offers ButterflyMX entry system for convenience, and a roof deck w/ panoramic city views. Situated in the heart of South Beach, 200 Townsend offers east access to Oracle Park, Chase Center, Caltrain, trendy restaurants, the Embarcadero and more!

property_description: Opportunity abounds w/ this delightful diamond in the rough positioned on a deep lot featuring 2-beds, 1-bath, formal living & dining rms, eat-in kitchen, spacious garage, developable rms downstairs, and an expansive rear yard! A gated tunnel entrance & stairwell w/ a lg skylight welcomes you into this cozy east-facing residence. The home boasts a traditional layout w/ a lovely formal foyer, a spacious living rm w/ wood-burn. frplc, an adjacent formal dining rm, a lg kitchen w/ lofty skylight, brand new gas range oven & fridge, a vintage bathroom w/ tub & separate stall shower, and 2 good-sized west-facing bedrooms w/ garden outlooks & large walk-in closets. Interior access from the central hallway leads to the spacious garage, laundry area, and multiple unwarranted rms awaiting your personal touch. Bring your contractor, color palette, and imagination because this is the one you have been waiting for! Add'l features: multiple closets, newly refinished hardwood floors, newly painted interior, new plush carpeting in the bedrooms, lovely crown moldings, and an incredibly deep backyard w/ mature trees & masonry fencing. Ideal location on the border of Mission Terr & Bernal Hts, close to Glen Park Village, Glen Canyon Park, BART, highways 101/280 & more! A commuter's dream come true!

property_description: This charming turn-key Victorian, built circa 1890, is full of character and options for extended family or potential rental income. It boasts an upper level with warm hardwood floors, high ceilings, abundant period details, double parlor, an open kitchen ideal for entertaining, complemented by a generous bathroom, laundry, and two well-appointed bedrooms. The modern and bright lower level of this home, with its own separate entrance, has a kitchenette, a full bathroom, 3 rooms with closets, a large laundry room and a living room that opens to a garden patio. The property features a tranquil oasis of lush landscaping in front and back, a large redwood deck with hills and distant ocean views, updated windows, fresh paint, and artistic touches throughout. A true San Francisco jewel, the home is perfectly located less than one block from McLaren Park, with over 300 acres of forested trails, bike paths, playgrounds, and dog parks. There is easy access to 101 and 280, and Mission Street restaurants and shops are a 10-minute walk.
Directions to Property: Turn onto Brazil Ave from Mission St and head west. Turn right on the Prague and property is on right.

property_description: Fabulous condominium in the heart of Noe Valley! With a private entrance, this peaceful residence features dark hardwood flooring, beautiful moldings, and floor to ceiling windows. The heart of the home is the gorgeous kitchen/family room. The open kitchen centers around a large island with sink and chic pendants overhead, and the kitchen is equipped with deluxe stainless appliances, tile backsplash, and a built-in pantry cabinet. Off the kitchen is a dining area with sliding glass doors out to the deck, and an inviting living room with gas fireplace. Another set of sliding doors lead out to the serene, covered deck. This private space is perfect for al fresco dining and entertaining in all seasons, and stairs lead down to the lovely backyard, boasting a fire pit and seating and dining areas. There are two generous bedrooms, one with a bay window facing greenery, and the other with a large closet. Off the hallway is an additional office/nursery, plus an attractive bath with a double vanity and shower over tub, and a toilet room and sink next door. The unit also includes a substantial basement storage room. This boutique 2-unit building is located just blocks from 24th Street's dining and shopping.

property_description: At 934 Portola, beauty meets comfort in San Leandro's sought-after Floresta Gardens. This stunning home boasts a lush garden oasis enchanting you upon arrival. Step inside to discover a meticulously maintained residence exuding pride of ownership. This charming abode offers ample space for relaxation & everyday living. The spacious living areas are bathed in natural light, creating an inviting atmosphere for hosting & quiet evenings at home. Notable updates include crown molding, updated windows & doors, sun tunnels & new fridge & tub. A Ring security system & outdoor outlets add modern convenience. The backyard features a patio deck, perfect for entertaining, & a hot tub for ultimate relaxation. The lush flowering landscaping adds to the home's charm & tranquility. The large lot provides room for outdoor enjoyment, whether you're entertaining guests, gardening, or basking in the tranquility of your surroundings. Park your vehicles with ease in the 2-car garage, & utilize the driveway for 2 additional cars. Nestled amidst serene streets, enjoy a peaceful retreat while still being close to the vibrant amenities of San Leandro. Enjoy a leisurely stroll to nearby Burrell Fields, indulge in retail therapy at Marina Square Shopping Center & stay active at the nearby 24-Hour Fitness.

property_description: Incredible development opportunity in Corona Heights! 260 Castro St has approved plans that are paid for and ready to be picked up from DBI (per seller). This parcel must be sold and developed with the adjacent parcel which also has approved plans, 262 Castro St. This double lot development has architectural plans crafted by Geddes Ulinskas Architects and calls for the development of four residences totaling 7, 828 sq. ft.: a) two 3-bedroom condominiums at 1, 963 sq. ft. and 1, 787 sq. ft., b) one 2-bedroom standalone single family home cottage at 1, 680 sq. ft., and c) one 3-bedroom single-family home at 2, 398 sq. ft. The homes will include Downtown VIEWS as well as 1-car parking for each home. Roof decks, terraces, and gardens are included in the plans. A 2-bedroom, 1-bathroom single family home currently sits at the front of 260 Castro St, and a 2-bedroom, 2-bathroom single family cottage sits at the rear of the parcel of 262 Castro St. Located in a highly-sought after location at the axis of Corona Heights, The Castro, and Duboce Triangle, the location of this opportunity affords the developer to command a premium price for the completed homes. The full construction package includes shoring and interior design plans. Images are digital renderings, buyers to investigate.
Directions to Property: Castro St between 16th St & Beaver.

property_description: Step through the lush, garden patio to this freestanding, bi-level cottage. Windows on all four sides flood the space with light and outlooks are full of greenery and mature palms. Set back from the street with a secure, locked gated entrance for added security. The first level welcomes you with a comfortable living room and gas fireplace, a fully equipped kitchen with a new gas range, dishwasher & washer/dryer, plus a renovated full bathroom. The upper level holds the 2 bedrooms and a renovated half bath. A ladder in the primary bedroom leads to an additional storage space coupled with a built-in safe. New light fixtures, hardwood floors, charming period details and recent seismic upgrade to front building that houses the garage. One independent parking space in the garage. Living in the highly sought after Cow Hollow neighborhood offers a vibrant & coveted lifestyle in the heart of San Francisco. This upscale neighborhood offers easy access to the breathtaking waterfront of the Marina District, Crissy Field & Fort Mason. You'll also appreciate the proximity to the hip & bustling Union, Chestnut, and Fillmore streets, where you'll find an endless array of shops, restaurants, markets, bars, spas and many other entertainment options! Walk Score: 98 Bike Score: 92

property_description: Come visit this panoramic view residence atop San Francisco's prestigious Nob Hill. You'll be greeted by views of our City's most iconic landmarks out of the condo's floor-to-ceiling windows. From the waters of the Bay, to Nob Hill's stunningly beautiful architectural treasures, beyond to the Downtown skyline, & even a peek of the Bay Bridge; the views rival those of condominiums priced at millions more. In fact, the price-point & value of this two bedroom, two bath condo are unmatched. With a creative vision, this Gramercy Towers jewel can be transformed into a sweet high-rise sanctuary, worthy of the heritage & history of its Nob Hill environment. The Gramercy Towers provides premium services & amenities for its residents, including a front desk concierge, a fitness center, indoor pool, jetted hot tub, men's & women's locker rooms, spacious lobby, gated courtyard, & more. The best of SF is at your doorstep with Nob Hill's year-round event programming, the iconic Cable Cars, & much more. Plus, the Gramercy is just blocks away from downtown, Union Square, Chinatown & North Beach, grocery stores, parks, restaurants, cafs, & health care services; making this apartment a quintessential San Francisco home. Please note that the furnishings used in the photos are virtually rendered.
Directions to Property: Head east on California and once you cross Jones Street, The Gramercy Towers is located on the southwest corner. You may park in the gated courtyard for 15 minutes during your showing.

property_description: 500 Ellington, in the same family for nearly 50 years, has been thoughtfully renewed inside and out, and is ready for its next caretakers. This turnkey 2-bedroom / 1-bathroom single-family home occupies a corner lot. Vintage terrazzo steps lead to a foyer with coat closet. The front-facing living room features corner windows with views from Sutro Tower to McLaren Park, and the formal dining room is great to gather for festive and everyday meals. The eat-in kitchen has brand-new stainless-steel appliances, abundant cabinets, and counter space on every wall. Enjoy peaceful neighborhood views and space for a small island or breakfast nook. At the rear of the home, find two spacious bedrooms, each with good natural light, large closets, and refinished wood floors. The adjacent renovated bathroom and a linen closet complete this level. Internal stairs lead to the lower level, with 2 side-by-side garage spots, a deep storage closet, and a laundry area with sink. This floor also includes a generous bonus room - use it as an office, playroom, guest space, or base for future expansion. The backyard includes a patio with planter beds and peekaboo views of Salesforce Tower. Easy access to the freeway and public transit, Mission Street shops and restaurants, and schools and playgrounds.

property_description: Prestigious Pacific Heights location with stunning bay views on all levels define this extraordinary 7 bedroom, 7.5 bathroom residence. Designed by renowned San Francisco architect Bernard Joseph, the home's thoughtful layout spans three levels and seamlessly blends meticulous craftsmanship with modern luxury. The top and middle levels each offer full-floor homes with 3 bedrooms, 3 bathrooms (2 ensuite), formal living and dining rooms, and modern amenities. The top floor features a grand skylight, eat-in chef's kitchen, and an enclosed atrium. The middle floor boasts a fully remodeled kitchen with butler pantry. An exceptional 1 bed, 1.5 bath housekeeping unit includes a private entrance and opens onto a charming garden with bay views. The expansive rooftop deck and garden blend indoor and outdoor living, creating ideal spaces for entertaining or relaxing. An elevator provides convenient access to all three levels of the home. Situated on a coveted and level block of Pacific Avenue, this home sits on a wide and deep 37' x 128' lot. This is a rare opportunity to own a piece of San Francisco history, with unparalleled views and an impeccable design that stands the test of time.

property_description: Compass Commercial is pleased to present for sale, 4505 - 4507 Mission Street, in San Francisco is a 5 unit mixed use building in the Mission Terrace/Excelsior District. The property has three leased units and two pending lease units, leaving the option open for a buyer to occupy units or lease to generate more income. This is a two story walk up that also includes a back yard. The ground floor retail is leased on a month to month basis. The 2nd Floor has two studio's and two single room occupant with a shared bathroom. The units are all separately metered w/ PG&E. This is a prominent location on a main commercial corridor w/ many neighboring retail, service, and restaurant businesses. McLaren Park, Bart, and Freeway Entrances are close by. property_description: Incredible development opportunity in Corona Heights! 262 Castro St has approved plans that are paid for and ready to be picked up from DBI (per seller). This parcel must be sold and developed with the adjacent parcel which also has approved plans, 260 Castro St. This double lot development has architectural plans crafted by Geddes Ulinskas Architects and calls for the development of four residences totaling 7, 828 sq. ft.: a) two 3-bedroom condominiums at 1, 963 sq. ft. and 1, 787 sq. ft., b) one 2-bedroom standalone single family home cottage at 1, 680 sq. ft., and c) one 3-bedroom single-family home at 2, 398 sq. ft. The homes will include Downtown VIEWS as well as 1-car parking for each home. Roof decks, terraces, and gardens are included in the plans. A 2-bedroom, 1-bathroom single family home currently sits at the front of 260 Castro St, and a 2-bedroom, 2-bathroom single family cottage sits at the rear of the parcel of 262 Castro St. Located in a highly-sought after location at the axis of Corona Heights, The Castro, and Duboce Triangle, the location of this opportunity affords the developer to command a premium price for the completed homes. The full construction package includes shoring and interior design plans. Images are digital renderings, buyers to investigate.
Directions to Property: Castro St between 16th St & Beaver.

property_description: This polished 3-bedroom, 2-bath co-op unit in a prestigious 12 unit building, blends modern elegance with historic charm, offering a truly unique and luxurious living experience in desirable Pacific Heights. An open floor plan connects the gracious foyer, living room and dining room with direct access to an inviting sunroom & private deck. Chef's kitchen boasts high-end stainless-steel appliances, sleek granite countertops, custom cabinetry, inspiring your inner culinary passion. Convenient butler's pantry off the kitchen. Retreat to primary suite with walk-in closet, spa-like en-suite bathroom. The third bedroom is equally inviting as a home office/den.Features modern conveniences of in-unit laundry, hardwood floors, recessed lighting, and ample storage space. Relax on your private deck, perfect for morning coffee/evening cocktails. Elevator to garage pkg & storage. Access San Francisco's finest dining, shopping, and cultural landmarks. Enjoy convenience of nearby Lafayette Park, Whole Foods, & bustling Fillmore Street. HOA dues include heat, water, trash, maintenance, resident manager, and insurance. property_description: This large 3-bedroom, 2-bath condo combines a gracious scale with beautiful architectural details. The inviting front steps lead through fluted columns to the sheltered entry. From the welcoming foyer you are drawn to the living room, which spans the front of the home. It is flooded with natural light from the oversized bay windows overlooking the verdant street trees. The living room and adjacent dining room each have fireplaces with stunning mantelpieces; both are comfortable rooms for daily living, but also lend themselves to entertaining on an epic scale. The large formal dining room has stately built-ins and is ideal for gracious dinner parties. The recently renovated eat-in kitchen has ample cabinetry, counter space and stainless steel appliances. A full bath is conveniently located off the hall which leads to the three bedrooms. The primary suite, with a private, en-suite bath, overlooks the garden and green belt. The second bedroom also overlooks the backyard and is connected to the third by a passage with a conveniently located vanity room with washbasin. In-unit laundry and additional secure storage offer added convenience. Golden Gate Park, Buena Vista Park, Haight and Cole Valley are all within a few blocks.

Located in the Summit, one of San Francisco's most prestigious buildings, a mid-century Eichler, this corner unit has an oversized living room showcasing the incredible views, and opening onto a large deck that runs the length of the unit and is also accessed by both bedrooms.The cozy view dining area is adjacent to the well-equipped and newly remodeled kitchen, equipped with chic cabinetry and gorgeous stone countertops and backsplash as well as new stainless steel appliances, including a dishwasher, range, and built in microwave. The primary bedroom, with fabulous views, has a spacious and timeless bathroom featuring richly-veined stones and a modern glass enclosed shower, as well as a walk-in closet with ample hanging space. The second bedroom is a good size, along with similarly stunning outlooks. This bedroom is served by a full bathroom that doubles as a guest bath, also with classic stone finishes and featuring a shower over tub. 1-car parking in the secure garage, storage, and a 24-hour doorman and professional management, make this the epitome of luxury living, close to the vibrant shops and restaurants of Russian Hill.

The bottom residence presents the option for a room expansion elevating value and tailored functionality. The topmost residence boasts views and a private balcony, offering an exclusive private outdoor area. A serene backyard and patio provide an ideal setting for an idyllic landscaped garden perfect for entertaining and relaxing. Two blocks from Golden Gate Park, residents can enjoy easy access to urban hikes, running and biking paths, children's parks, and museums. The Inner Sunset's vibrant neighborhood offers culturally rich restaurants, charming boutiques, cafes, and artisanal bars. Highway 1 and MUNI provide convenient access to all Bay Area destinations: Downtown San Francisco, Golden Gate Bridge, the Great Highway, and I-280 to the South Bay.

property_description: 1959, the year 3431-3433 22nd Street was constructed, was marked by a modern aesthetic in architecture, with buildings having smooth, flattened facades, often demarcated by different planes rather than physical decoration. Located in a row of housing likely built around the same time, this building is no exception. The decorative aspect of the faade is an inset vertical rectangle, highlighted by color, which suggests a certain separation of space within. The current owners took the interior down to the studs and recreated a modern space, but this time with more open entertaining rooms, separated by an arch that mimics the kitchen island lights and back-splash tiles. The curves both disrupt and complement the angular lines of the interior. Two generous bedrooms overlook the rear shared yard with the spacious hallway bathroom having a mirror-like effect caused by the floor-to-ceiling tile on the right wall as you enter. On the garage level is a bonus space used by the current owners as an office with an updated half-bath, all permitted in 2010. The shared yard includes a common gas burner, grill and sink. The location is exceptional, whether walking, biking, or driving to one's chosen destination.
Directions to Property: On 22nd between Dolores and Guerrero
Master Bathroom Features: Window, Tub w/Shower Over, Tile, Radiant Heat, Dual Flush Toilet

property_description: The Victorian facade of this classic Pacific Heights home shows beautiful architectural detail, and the front garden beckons you to the sheltered porch. Upon entering, the living room and adjacent dining room make a stunning impression, with unusually high ceilings, wainscoting, molding, and a marble fireplace. Flooded with sunshine from bay windows, the corner location provides abundant natural light from three sides. The first bedroom, at the front, could also serve as an office/nursery. The primary bedroom, also on this level, has an en-suite bath. Flowing seamlessly from these gracious rooms into the more contemporary spaces, there is a modern, open living space towards the back with eat-in kitchen, family room, full bath, and atrium. Accessed from the family room, the deck provides lofty outdoor space. The entire level begs to be used for gracious entertaining. The spacious lower level includes a second family room, two bedrooms, a large bath, laundry, and storage. With a private entrance, this is an ideal guest suite. With a premier location in a coveted neighborhood, it's minutes from the amenities of Fillmore and Sacramento. Rated a Walker's Paradise'', public transit is a mere block away, while the 2-car garage gives added convenience.

property_description: Built in 1943, this charming beach cottage nestled in San Francisco's Sunset District offers a cozy retreat with a nostalgic feel. Boasting 2 bedrooms, 1 bathroom, and a coveted 2-car garage (with room for 3rd car in driveway), it exudes vintage appeal with its classic architecture and original details. Inside, the cottage features hardwood floors that add warmth to the airy living spaces, complemented by large windows that invite natural light. The kitchen is charmingly updated with newer appliances, cabinetry, and fixtures, with access outside. The bathroom is also updated. Outside, a low-maintenance garden provides a serene escape ideal for relaxing or entertaining guests. Situated in a sought-after neighborhood known for its peaceful ambiance and proximity to Ocean Beach, this historic cottage offers not just a home, but a glimpse into San Francisco's coastal heritage. The garage level has storage rooms and is mostly undeveloped. Located 1/2 block to the Quintara bus line and just a few blocks to Noriega's bustling restaurants and shops.
Directions to Property: between Quintara and Rivera Streets

property_description: Discover the perfect blend of historic charm and modern amenities in this stunning mid-century 3 bedroom, 2 bath home located in the heart of Bernal Heights. Built in 1966, 445 Gates Street has been meticulously maintained and thoughtfully updated to provide a comfortable and stylish living experience. With a 2 car garage equipped with upgraded electrical ports, a dedicated laundry room/in-law, and gorgeous views of Holly Park from its oversized picture windows, this mid-century modern home has lots to offer. The master bedroom on the ground floor is separated by a traditional landing, with an ensuite bathroom. The upper 2 bedrooms harbor a sweet encompassing view of the backyard garden. 445 Gates Street is just far enough from the 101 and the 280, and the surrounding streets offer unique and inspiring walks, from mini walking bridges connecting neighborhoods and hidden slides and swings to an urban sustainable farm that is open to the public for tours, education, and support. Nestled between 4 major parks (Bernal Heights Hill, Precita Park, Holly Park, and St. Mary's Park), 445 Gates Street is a cozy and roomy 2 story home!

property_description: Capturing the romantic spirit of the Victorian era, Inn San Francisco, one of the most beloved San Francisco bed and breakfasts, invites you to be our guest and discover comfort and hospitality with warmth that is distinctly San Franciscan. Step back in time into our 1872 mansion. Our bed and breakfast provides a generous breakfast buffet in the grand double parlors or garden patio. The property features antiques, fresh flowers, a sundeck and hot tub, telephones, HDTVs, and select parking available at the hotel. Originally built on Mansion Row, our historic twenty-seven-room Italianate Victorian inn was the home of John English, his wife, and their seven children. English, a San Francisco City Commissioner, dubbed The Potato King'' for his vast holdings in potato commodities, also raised champion racehorses on the surrounding grounds. Every year since 2011, our Inn has received the honor of the TripAdvisor Certificate of Excellence award. See for yourself why our guests rate our accommodations so highly, whether you are seeking San Francisco accommodations for a relaxing vacation, corporate business, or visiting family or friends, our aim is to make your stay with us and the City of San Francisco a most pleasurable one.

property_description: Vibrant and stylish 3BD/2BA Condo in South San Francisco. With 1290sqft of space plus balcony, this residence offers a perfect blend of comfort and modern living. Stepping inside, you'll be greeted by a spacious layout that combines functionality and charm. The primary bedroom provides a serene retreat, complete with an en-suite bathroom. Well appointed kitchen with granite countertops and modern stainless-steel appliances, all seamlessly connected to the spacious living and dining area. Condo amenities include a fitness center, clubhouse lounge, a toddler playground and BART Shuttle Service. Safeway and Westborough Square are just across the street, with cafes, restaurants and shopping. This is an affordable below market rate (BMR) unit through the City of South San Francisco's Affordable Home Buyer Program and is subject to income restrictions, resale controls, monitoring, & other restrictions apply. Maximum household incomes cannot exceed 100% of the San Mateo County Area Median Income. Maximum income for 3 person = $167, 950; 4 = $186, 600; 5 = $201, 550; 6= $216, 450; 7=$231, 400. Prospective BMR buyers shall submit a complete pre-screen application to start the eligibility process. Incomplete applications will not be reviewed. APPLICATION DEADLINE: July 23, 2024 by 12pm.

property_description: Perched near the top of Collingwood Hill, 850 Castro Street has panoramic downtown and bay views from the living and dining rooms, kitchen, primary bedroom and the family room! Bright sunlight floods these rooms during the day; City and East Bay lights twinkle at night. This family home is easily accessed using the private drive on Collingwood Street (#433) which leads to the garage and back door. Built in the 1920s, this Marina style home has a generous open living/dining room with fireplace, sky-lit kitchen, and two spacious bedrooms (one with a deck) sharing a bath on the main floor. The mid-level provides convenient interior access to the garage, an office, secluded primary suite, and laundry area. The lower level has a spacious family/media room, and easy access to the garden area facing Castro Street from the formal front door entry. Recently remodeled, this home is move-in ready! Property access is easiest via private drive adjacent to 433 Collingwood. Do not drive in - park nearby and walk in for viewing.
Directions to Property: Access via private drive adjacent to 433 Collingwood...park at 21st and Collingwood and walk in as there is no parking for guests. There is a lockbox on the private drive side (rear door) of the property accessed via Collingwood Street.

property_description: Welcome to this iconic Mediterranean Revival masterpiece, built in 1924 and available for the first time in 50 years. Within walking distance to the serene Lake Merritt, this grand residence offers a unique blend of historic charm and modern potential. Home is filled with original architectural details that captivate at every turn. Hardwood floors, oversized arched windows for natural light and AMAZING VIEWS. Main floor includes large rooms, charming fireplace, while the kitchen and baths await your personal touch to bring them to modern standards. Flexible space with outside access on first floor has one-bedroom, full bath and laundry room for potential ADU and flat space over 2-car garage for potential future build, both subject to city approval. The interior and exterior have been freshly painted. Outdoors, a beautiful garden, adorned with mature fruit trees, provides a tranquil retreat. Don't miss this rare opportunity to own architectural history in one of the city's most desirable neighborhoods. Embrace the charm, envision the updates, and make this iconic home your own.
Directions to Property: Lakeshore Ave, Turn left onto Wesley Ave, Turn right onto Merritt Ave, Turn right onto Prospect Ave

property_description: Introducing an extraordinary mixed-use property meticulously designed to accommodate the concept of live-work spaces. This newer construction showcases a blend of modern architecture and timeless elegance. Each unit offers a comfortable and private haven, featuring 20' ceilings and skylights, an Italian kitchen with matte taupe finishes, a 13' waterfall island, a private patio, and a secluded backyard. Every detail, from the carefully selected fixtures to the innovative use of space, reflects a commitment to both form and function. Formerly occupied as housing for UC Berkeley students, the property boasts a range of well-appointed rooms and communal areas for social gatherings and interactions. Located in North Oakland on the Rockridge/Temescal border, and minutes away from restaurants, coffee shops, Rockridge BART Station, highways 13, 24, 580 & 880.

Kitchen features finished skylight; built-in, new, electric stove top; lots of cupboard space; built-in self-cleaning oven; dishwasher; and roll out storage & pantry drawers. The hallway with large skylight leads to remodeled main bathroom with tiled shower, double vanity sink, ample storage, & skylight. Home is three bedrooms: 2 have built-in closets, and 1 has lovely oak armoire and opens to balcony which leads to the rear yard with shed, possibilities for a dream garden. Convenient powder room was added on main level. A huge tandem plus garage with a spacious bonus room, laundry area, workshop and storage space are a dream come true with so much flexibility and space. Garage has been firewalled, insulated and Sheetrocked. Richmond District home is well-located, one block to GG Park. Home has been lovingly maintained by the same family for decades.

property_description: Residential Lot Unique Ocean Development-We believe this will not ever happen again. A development of 10 lots (now 8 available) located on a bluff dominating the Pacific Ocean. Land along the ocean is regulated by the California Coastal Commission and so it is extremely difficult to build along the ocean. Ohlone Point represents the culmination of many years of working with local authorities and interest groups to get the necessary permissions to create this unique development. Ranging from 1.2 to over 2 acres, each avails of breathtaking, unobstructed, ocean views for miles up and down the California Coast. Each lot is already set up with paved, beautifully lit streets, driveway entrances, public city sewer, city water and PG&E. Minutes away from the sands of Rockaway Beach and local beachfront restaurants. A haven with the most stunning ocean views, backing onto hundreds of acres of open space, yet only a short drive to downtown San Francisco, SFO Airport, Sand Hill Road, Stanford and the Peninsula.
Topography: Cleared, Coast, Gently Sloped, Hillside, Lot Grade Varies, Mostly Level
Directions to Property: Take 101 south to Fassler; left onto Fassler then right onto Roberts and first left will bring you to the gates. Fassler Gates are not good for access.
Development Status: Public Report Available, Design Review Required

property_description: Situated in the vibrant Inner Richmond neighborhood, this penthouse level three-bed, two-bath condominium is a true gem. Beautifully updated by the current owners, this property is enhanced by multiple skylights, tall ceilings and a coveted open floorplan. The spacious dining and living room area features a cozy gas fireplace and attached west-facing deck perfect for sunsets. Off the living room, there is also an office alcove ideal for working from home. The refreshed kitchen features a 6-burner range, built-in appliances and ample cabinet space. Down the hall, the secluded primary bedroom offers a large closet and dressing area. The luxuriously reimagined ensuite bath has a large soaking tub, dual sinks and a separate stall shower. Two gracious guest bedrooms and a thoughtfully designed second full bath allow flexibility and respite for guests, family or work. In-unit laundry, tankless water heater, one-car independent parking and a shared yard are also included. The 3-unit building is conveniently located next to Clement Street, bustling with shops, restaurants, entertainment, and the popular Sunday farmers market. Mountain Lake Park and the Presidio are just moments away.

property_description: A modern home, nestled on a flat block on the coveted East slope of Bernal Heights. The entry-level bedroom is a versatile flex space with garden access, perfect for a home office or guest room. The laundry is also located on this level with a 1/2 bath. On the main level, an open floor plan showcases a designer chef's kitchen including a Thermador appliance package. Don't miss the artful Heath Tile backsplash. Adjacent is a dining area, powder room and a spacious, elegant living room with a vaulted ceiling, offering ample room for daily activities and entertaining, with a beautiful fireplace as a focal point. Located on the upper level, the primary ensuite bedroom features another fireplace, and space for a cozy sitting area, creating a perfect retreat. Down the hall, you'll find another full bathroom and a spacious bedroom. This green home is a testament to modern design and sustainability. The roof was replaced in 2023, includes energy efficient solar panels. There is also a solar Water Heater and an EV charger in the garage. The home has a selection of both double & triple paned windows. Enjoy the surrounding secret staircase and gardens, the vibrant Alemany Farmers Market, Cortland Ave and the community feel of The Bernal Neighborhood.

property_description: Step into this charming two-level 2BR/1BA TIC unit located in a beautiful 8-unit Edwardian building, offering a perfect blend of classic elegance and modern convenience. The stunning lower-level features abundant natural light through large, picturesque windows overlooking a large private deck adorned with lush landscaping, creating an ideal oasis for relaxation and entertainment. The open floor plan seamlessly combines the kitchen and dining/living area. With two bedrooms, one bath, on the upper level and a cozy carpeted interior, this condo exudes comfort, privacy and tranquility. The rear bedroom overlooks the deck, exclusive to this unit. Situated across from Alta Plaza Park, enjoy easy access to outdoor activities. Walk to Fillmore's fine dining, shopping and transportation. Easy access to the Marina, Chestnut and Sacramento St. Laurel Heights shopping and the Financial District. The property also includes parking for one small car and a storage unit, providing practical amenities for city living. Having been lovingly maintained by the current owner for 38 years, this home carries a rich history and a sense of pride, making it a unique find in a sought-after location.
Directions to Property: Divisadero to Clay St.

property_description: Discover this charming 3-bedroom, 1.5-bathroom flat in the heart of Hayes Valley! Situated in an impeccably maintained building, this residence boasts high ceilings, exquisite stained glass windows, and bay windows offering unexpected downtown views. The triple-paned windows ensure a serene and quiet living environment. Step into the newly remodeled kitchen, featuring Caesarstone countertops and stylish subway tile, perfect for culinary enthusiasts. The updated bathroom showcases elegant subway tile and double showerheads, adding a touch of luxury to your daily routine. Conveniently plumbed for an in-unit washer and dryer, laundry day is a breeze. This flat also includes a huge exclusive-use storage room and a shared bike room, catering to all your storage needs. The location is unbeatable, just steps away from Hayes Valley's vibrant shopping scene, world-class dining, and a plethora of cultural options. Enjoy nearby Alta Plaza Park, Golden Gate Park, and the famous Wiggle bike route. With a Transit Score of 100 and Bike and Walk Score of 99, commuting is a breeze.Experience the perfect blend of historic charm and modern convenience. A great value and a must-see to believe!
Directions to Property: Easy to park on Oak! Go down Oak towards Octavia property is on the right hand side between Buchanan and Laguna.

property_description: This extensively remodeled condo showcases one of the most beautiful marble-clad kitchen & bathrooms at the Four Seasons Hotel & Residences! Located on the southwest corner of the tower, #25G features an open layout combining kitchen/living/dining areas to expand views spanning the Bay & Yerba Buena Gardens to City Hall & Twin Peaks. Front doors open to stunning bamboo floors & gallery that lead to entertaining areas. Here, the kitchen showcases monochromatic colors, counters of full-slab Calacatta marble, custom cabinetry, and backsplashes of an exquisite, mosaic-patterned tile. The large-scale primary suite is outfitted with oversized southern windows - complete with dual solar shades - and a walk-in closet. The opulent marble-clad bathroom includes dual vanities, tub, large shower, & water closet. The guest bedroom also enjoys southern views with a gorgeous bathroom, also clad in stone. Infrastructure includes electric shades, multiple flat-screens, and in-home laundry. Four Seasons Hotel amenities include anticipatory concierge, friendly door staff & world-class security, 24/7 in-room dining, housekeeping, the dynamic MKT restaurant & lounge, & the onsite 127, 000sf Equinox fitness center. Located steps from the city's best museums, shopping, cafes, & restaurants.

Nestled in The Dogpatch, one of San Francisco's most coveted neighborhoods, this rare top floor gem offers a luminous sanctuary of modern living in a boutique 40-residence building constructed in 2019. Embrace The Dogpatch's vibrant energy, named one of the Top 50 Coolest Neighborhoods in the World by Time-Out. An eclectic mix of art galleries, trendy boutiques, and renowned eateries are just outside your doorstep. Discover contemporary design with wood plank floors, sleek finishes, and abundant natural light. The gourmet kitchen features high-end Bosch appliances. Two bedrooms and two bathrooms, with a master bath featuring a walk-in shower. Convenient in-unit stackable washer-dryer and central heating/AC for year-round comfort. Indulge in the ultimate outdoor retreat on the shared expansive rooftop terrace, which includes a fire pit, al fresco dining, landscaped decking, and stunning views. Two built-in BBQ areas and a TV alcove enhance luxury living. The property includes one-car designated parking, access to a bicycle storage room. Head to downtown SF via waterfront bike path or public transportation. The close by 280 freeway affords easy access to SFO and the Peninsula. An exceptional residence representing the best of urban sophistication in a highly sought-after locale.

property_description: Pride of ownership is evident in this charming 1920s home, set on a quiet Noe Valley block. It features 3BR, 3BA, and approximately 1851 sqft. Newly refinished hardwood floors greet you in the foyer, which has ample space for a bench. The living room, with Marina-style windows, a wood-burning fireplace, and coved ceilings, flows seamlessly into the dining room and kitchen. The kitchen boasts stainless steel counters, stainless appliances, and a wine refrigerator. The upper level has 2BR with en-suite baths and deck access. The rear bedroom offers an idyllic view of Twin Peaks. Skylights flood the kitchen and stairway with sunlight, leading down to the lower level where you'll discover a sanctuary-like primary suite. French doors open directly from the bedroom to the garden. The primary's remodeled bathroom has a large soaking tub, glass-enclosed shower, double sink counter, and a well appointed walk-in closet. On the same level, you'll find a laundry room with abundant storage and an efficient layout for folding clothes. Additionally, there's a spacious garage with convenient interior access to the home.

property_description: Resort-style living in the heart of Foster City! Come see this beautiful 3-bedroom, 2.5-bathroom townhome in Foster City's sought-after Isle Cove neighborhood offering the perfect blend of comfort and resort-style living. Imagine relaxing on one of your two private patios, with a swimming pool, tennis courts, and the serene waterfront just steps away. Step inside to a freshly painted interior, upgraded dual pane windows and sliders, recessed lighting, stainless steel appliances, new stove, new washer, and gleaming kitchen cabinets. Enjoy the convenience of an indoor laundry room and ample storage space throughout, including a 2-car garage with a brand-new epoxy coating. Upstairs you will find a large primary bedroom with a spacious en-suite bathroom, two more spacious bedrooms, and another full bathroom. property_description: Welcome to 1534 7th Avenue, a Lovely, original 1916 Craftsman Home. The pictures will show you the beautiful wood-trim features throughout the home. Main Floor consists of spacious Entry Foyer, Living Room with Fireplace, remarkable 3-dimensional Hardwood Floor inlays, adjoining Dining Room with wooden Hutch and outside views of rear Deck and grand upsloped Garden. Step into the original Kitchen which you will love to re-configure to fit your own wants and needs. You will also re-imagine the most recent use of the rear porch as a Kitchen adjunct. You may simply step out of this porch area onto a previously mentioned lovely Deck space, with access to the colorful rear garden. Returning to the Entry Foyer simply ascend the interior staircase to the upstairs full-width Master Bedroom with double closets, second and third rear Bedrooms, and a good-sized Bathroom with a vintage claw-foot bathtub and overhead skylight. The expansive basement/garage parking level has lots of space for storage, workbench area, parking etc. There is a separate tradesmen's walkway leading from the street access to the rear yard. This is a HOME in every sense of the word. Come see why it should be your new Home.

property_description: A world-class architectural collaboration of John Maniscalco & David Oldroyd/ODADA, this glass-walled, modernist masterpiece reveals dynamic 270-degree views from Alcatraz to the Bay Bridge to Twin Peaks. Created within Russian's Hill's mid-century 1750 Taylor, #1703's sophisticated infrastructure & serene palette of materials & colors were designed with one purpose: to live harmoniously amidst the mesmerizing five-county views. Detailed with oversized mahogany panels, pocket doors, & translucent glass panels, the aerie's versatile walls open to expand vistas, or close for privacy. The living room shares glass walls with the dining area & its floor-to-ceiling abstract wine tower. The quartz-clad kitchen features appliances that disappear behind blind bifold doors. The richly paneled library/flexible guest room includes an elegant powder bath. Divisible in two, the opulent primary suite hosts dual baths. Amplifying the nighttime cityscape are uplight channels on floors & LED cove lighting. Royal Towers residents enjoy a fitness center & heated pool with a retractable roof. Its majestic owner's club with soaring ceilings & landmark views were all recently redesigned. A 24/7 doorman, attentive staff, & professional management ensure one's time in the city is effortless & enjoyable.

property_description: 511 Leavenworth is an attractive Downtown San Francisco property consisting of 17 units. The building consists of 8 studios and 8 one-bedroom units plus a small commercial store front. In addition, there is a garage with allows for 7 car parking. This attractive property is located on Leavenworth Street between O'Farrell and Geary in the Downtown district. It is walking distance to Union Square, the nearby Civic Center, and shopping, hospitals, restaurants, retail and many other options. Public transportation opportunities are excellent. Significant is the fact that there have been over $1, 000, 000 in renovations in 2005 which include updated wiring, plumbing, roofing, skylights and many other updates. The majority of the units were updated at that time. Constructed in 1921, the building measures 11, 352 square feet per appraisal. The property is separately metered for gas and electric. Heat is provided by a steam heat boiler. There is a washer/dryer combination in the basement area The low frequency fire alarm horns have been installed as well. 511 Leavenworth offers investors tremendous upside potential and considerable upgrades in a Downtown property which has been professionally managed.

It is walking distance to Union Square, the nearby Civic Center, and shopping, hospitals, restaurants, retail and many other options. Public transportation opportunities are excellent. Significant is the fact that there have been over $1, 000, 000 in renovations in 2005 which include updated wiring, plumbing, roofing, skylights and many other updates. Heat is provided by a steam heat boiler.
